# Documentation Standards

## Language and tone

- Write in English for all reference content (CLI, config, guides).
- Use complete sentences; avoid telegraphic bullet chains.
- Commands must be copy-paste ready — no `...` omissions in code blocks.

## Structure

| Directory | Purpose | Edit manually? |
|-----------|---------|--------------|
| `cli/` | Command cheatsheets by topic | Yes |
| `guides/roles/` | Workflows by operator role | Yes |
| `guides/scales/` | Recommendations by cluster size | Yes |
| `config/` | Option tables from upstream YAML | No — run `scripts/generate-config.py` |
| `REFERENCE.md` | Main hub — sync to `docs/index.md` after edits |

## Linking

- Link to config options: `../config/<subsystem>/INDEX.md` or use `./scripts/lookup-config.sh`
- Link back to hub: `[← Reference](../REFERENCE.md)` or `../index.md` inside `docs/`
- Cross-link CLI ↔ config ↔ guides; do not duplicate large option tables in guides

## CLI pages

- Group by task, not alphabetically
- One command per line in fenced `bash` blocks
- Include `<placeholder>` for required args; `[optional]` for optional flags
- Add a “See also” line pointing to related config INDEX when relevant

## After editing REFERENCE.md

```bash
python3 scripts/sync-docs-index.py
```

## Do not

- Hand-edit generated files under `config/` except via regenerate script
- Add `Co-authored-by: Cursor` to commits
- Create duplicate README/OVERVIEW content — extend REFERENCE.md instead
